cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a solution for a small cell scenario, which involves wireless networking and communication. The paper discusses issues related to interference control and enhancing the number of concurrently supportable users, which are relevant to this sub-category.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of probability distribution and uncertain channel state information in designing the algorithm and interference control scheme, respectively. These concepts are related to information theory.
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions enhancing the user experience by saving energy and enshielding inhabitants. This is related to multimedia applications that require high-quality user experience.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a solution that involves controlling interference and enhancing the capacity of the system. These are related to systems and control.
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes an algorithm and interference control scheme that involve computational methods. This is related to computational engineering.
